{"key":"processedPost-12723777","value":{"id":12723777,"first":12723451,"last":12728797,"when":1276232225,"utime":"06/11/10 07:57 AM","content":"Spent coffee grinds are what you want to use.&nbsp; After they've brewed a pot of coffee, they can be mixed with the coir and/or verm and pasteurized.&nbsp; Don't use coffee grinds right out of the can.&nbsp; Your substrate will contaminate.<br />Don't use coir without pasteurizing.&nbsp; In addition, a mixture of 50/50 coir-verm makes an excellent substrate.&nbsp; Verm has food for fungi too in the form of minerals.&nbsp; It's also considered a 'fertilizer' for plants, so adding verm to any bulk substrate makes it better.&nbsp; Gypsum is also an excellent mineral additive.<br />RR","title":"Re: CCV recipe"}}